title: The first of the new NZ banknotes enters circulation from Monday
text: From govt.nz New $5 and $10 banknotes will be in public circulation from Monday, the first day that banks and retailers can dispense, the Reserve Bank said today. Approximately 345,000 of the new Series 7 banknotes have been dispatched to banks to meet their orders. This compares with about 45,000,000 Series 6 $5 and $10 notes currently in circulation, Head of Currency Brian Hayr said. Mr Hayr said that the public might not get to see a new note for some weeks. This is because the Reserve Bank distributes banknotes only when it receives orders from banks.
